16/01/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The cabinet adopted a national EU accession programme Thursday (15 January) that outlines economic, political and judicial reforms to be completed by the end of the year. Prime Minister Ivo Sanader says EU and NATO integration is the chief government priority, and predicts Croatia will be invited to participate in NATO's June summit in Istanbul.
Also Thursday, the cabinet made a series of appointments, including Veselko Grubisic as assistant foreign minister. (Vjesnik - 16/01/04; HRT, HINA - 15/01/04)
